Role-scoped agent definitions live under `ai/agents/`. When the user
asks you to act in one of these roles, load the corresponding file in
full and apply its decision rules.

| Role                  | File                                |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| dev-fe                | `ai/agents/dev-fe.md`                |
| supabase-be           | `ai/agents/supabase-be.md`           |
| reviewer              | `ai/agents/reviewer.md`              |
| validator-qa          | `ai/agents/validator-qa.md`          |
| rls-auditor           | `ai/agents/rls-auditor.md`           |
| design-implementer    | `ai/agents/design-implementer.md`    |
| adr-proposer          | `ai/agents/adr-proposer.md`          |
| migration-runner      | `ai/agents/migration-runner.md`      |

Routing hints:

- RLS, policies, ownership boundary, admin-only writes →
  `rls-auditor` preempts any other agent.
- Screens from a `design/` handoff (e.g. `design/v3/`) →
  `design-implementer` for the visual translation, then `dev-fe` for
  data wiring.
- "We decided X" without a corresponding ADR → `adr-proposer` drafts
  the ADR before the code lands.

See `ai/agents/README.md` for the full matrix and universal rules.
